.Dd $Mdocdate: August 6 2007 $
.Dt RMAIL 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm rmail
.Nd handle remote mail received via uucp
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm rmail
.Op Fl T
.Op Fl D Ar domain
.Ar user ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility interprets incoming mail received via
uucp, collapsing
.Dq From
lines in the form generated by
.Xr mail.local 8
into a single line of the form
.Dq return-path!sender ,
and passing the processed mail on to
.Xr sendmail 8 .
.Pp
.Nm
is explicitly designed for use with
uucp and
.Xr sendmail 8 .
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl D Ar domain
Change the domain.
The default domain is UUCP.
.It Fl T
Enter debugging mode.
.El
.Pp
.Sy Note:
uucp is not part of the base
.Ox
system.
It comes as part of the uucp suite,
and can be installed via
.Xr ports 7
or
.Xr packages 7 .
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mail.local 8 ,
.Xr sendmail 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility appeared in
.Bx 4.2 .
.Sh BUGS
.Nm
should not reside in
.Pa /bin .
